window.bookSummaryJSON = "<p>After 25 years serving as the human Monitor of the Interstellar Ark, Hermes, Orion is scheduled to be placed back into hibernation with the other crewmembers.</p> <p>Knowing he'll die there and be replaced before the ship's voyage is over, he decides that he won’t — can’t — accept that fate.</p> <p>Whatever it takes, Orion will escape Hermes and see what's beyond, even if it means defying the regulations of his only friend — the ship-wide artificial intelligence known as Dan.</p> <p>From the <i>Washington Post</i> and number one Audible best-selling duo, Rhett C. Bruno and Jaime Castle, comes a harrowing science fiction short story that will leave you questioning exactly what it means to be alive.</p>"; 
